                     <p> 
                        <pb n="503"/> <placeName key="place_113108">Fornham St Martin.</placeName> <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename>, son of
                  <persName>
                              <forename>Luke</forename> of <placeName key="place_104540">Bury St Edmunds (St. Edmund)</placeName>
                           </persName></persName>, 
                  grants for 18 marks to the <orgName key="org_105025">hospital of St. Saviour</orgName> nine acres of arable land in 
                        the fields of <placeName key="place_105486">Scihtfornham</placeName> [sic; endorsed: 'Suthfornham' and 'Sancti Martini'], paying annually for the same 9d. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1215" notAfter="1220" precision="low">c. 1215-20</origDate>.) 
                   [T. de Walsingham, warde of the Hosp.]
                  </p>
